Leggings</a> ; <a href="/db/item.html?item=10214">Wristband of the Brood</a>
;&nbsp; <a href="/db/item.html?item=12028">Shadowed Silk Pants</a> ;
<p><b>Updated Quests:</b>&nbsp; <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=1368">Enchanter
Twilight Pants</a> ;&nbsp; <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=1375">Necromancer
Twilight Belt</a> ;
<center>
<p><img SRC="wand_spun.gif" height=43 width=294>
<br><b>June 2, 2002</b></center>

<p>We've ended the free premium preview a day early.&nbsp; The premium
search features are very processor intensive features, which is why they
are pay features.&nbsp; Under normal load, the site handles them fine,
but freeing them up like that basically increased their usage ten fold,
so we were just constantly bogging down and crashing (of course if our
premium usage permanantly, as opposed to temporarily, increased ten fold,
we would purchase the additional servers needed to handle that).&nbsp;
It wasn't fair to our regular premium members to have the searches be so
slow and the features they are paying for working so poorly, so despite
our hope to keep them open for another day, they are now premium only again.&nbsp;
For those who were able to try them out, I hope you got at least a feel
for how nice they are to have.&nbsp; And for our premium members, I'm truly
sorry you had such problems over the past couple of days.
<center>
<p><img SRC="wand.gif" height=43 width=294>
<br><b>May 31, 2002</b></center>

<p>I know many of you wonder whether it is worth it to sign up for the
premium service.&nbsp; After all, the site is very useful even for those
who don't pay anything, so what could you possibly get on top of that to
make it worth paying even the minimal fee we charge?&nbsp; Well, we're
going to show you.&nbsp; Starting right now and continuing until about
5:00 on Monday, we are opening up most of the premium features to our non-premium
visitors for free.&nbsp; We're even turning off the ads to let you see
what that's like.&nbsp; We encourage you to take advantage of this.&nbsp;
Click on the <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/adv_search.html">advanced
equipment search</a> and <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/adv_qsearch.html">advanced
quest search</a> and try them out.&nbsp; Go to the <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/itemzone.html">items
by zone list</a> and check out how useful that is.&nbsp; If you don't have
an account yet, <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/user.html?action=create">create
one</a> (it's free) and then log in and <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/userinfo.html?x">create
a character</a>.&nbsp; That will let you use my personal favorite premium
features: the character upgrade search and the wish list.&nbsp; Those will
really blow you away.&nbsp; Try <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/charsearch.html">searching
for characters</a> on your server, or check out the <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html">journal
section</a> and think of how cool it would be to have one of your own.
And this preview doesn't even include the posting titles you can get, the
links from the items to the fashion tables, the ability to bookmark items
and your own @allakhazam.com e-mail address, which all come as part of
the full service.&nbsp; Please take full advantage of this opportunity
to completely explore all of the advanced features.&nbsp; Then ask yourself
if this is worth the price of a cup of Starbucks coffee or a single pint
of Guinness (prices go from only $3.33 a month for a 3 month subscription
down to less than $2.50 per month for a full year).&nbsp; We feel pretty
sure your answer will be "Hell Yes.&nbsp; I can't believe I've been missing
out on this".&nbsp; Then simply click on the <a href="https://secure.allakhazam.com/signup.cgi">sign
up button</a>, and go to our secure server to continue to enjoy these features
long after this free period ends.
<p>Just a note.&nbsp; Making this service free for a while means we have
the equivalent of 500,000 premium members using our system.&nbsp; Believe
me, if we had 500,000 premium members we would just go buy Dell or something
and have all the servers we wanted :).&nbsp; Well anyways, it means there
will be times when the system is a little slower than normal.&nbsp; One
reason we are running this over a weekend is that it is the time we normally
have the least load (with weekday afternoons being our heaviest load),
so to get the best view of the normal premium performance, try it out on
Saturday or Sunday.
<p>We also put up E3 screenshots from <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/news/sdetail939.html?story=939">Everquest:
Planes of Power</a> and <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/news/sdetail940.html?story=940">Shadowbane</a>.
<p><b>New Items:</b> <a href="/db/item.html?item=12371">Dismal Rage Long
Sword</a> ;&nbsp; <a href="/db/item.html?item=12370">Acrylia Reinforced
Belt</a> ;&nbsp; <a href="/db/item.html?item=12369">Crimson Darkscale Bracer</a>
;&nbsp; <a href="/db/item.html?item=12368">Radiant Heraldic Boots</a> ;
<a href="/db/item.html?item=12367">Radiant
Heraldic Bracer</a> ; <a href="/db/item.html?item=12366">Flame Tipped Acrylia
Arrow</a> ;
<p><b>New Quests:</b> <a href="/db/quest.html?quest=1898">Dismal Knight
Important Task</a> ;
